de.learnlib.api.logging

Class LoggingPropertyOracle<I,A extends net.automatalib.automata.concepts.Output<I,D>,P,D>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.learnlib.api.logging.LoggingPropertyOracle<I,A,P,D>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - the input type
    A - the automaton type
    P - the property type
    D - the output type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    EquivalenceOracle<A,I,D>, InclusionOracle<A,I,D>, PropertyOracle<I,A,P,D>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LoggingPropertyOracle.DFALoggingPropertyOracle, LoggingPropertyOracle.MealyLoggingPropertyOracle

    public class LoggingPropertyOracle<I,A extends net.automatalib.automata.concepts.Output<I,D>,P,D>
extends Object
implements PropertyOracle<I,A,P,D>
    A PropertyOracle that performs logging. This class will log whenever the property is disproved, or when a counterexample to an automaton is found (i.e. a spurious counterexample is found).
    Author:
    Jeroen Meijer
